<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="167" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,310,535,561]" box="[189,310,535,561]" pageId="4" pageNumber="167">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,535,561]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="167" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,535,561]" pageId="4" pageNumber="167">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,581,643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="167">
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang, 2022" authorityName="Wang" authorityYear="2022" box="[544,690,582,608]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Antiochtha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erromera" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[544,690,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="167">A. erromera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[697,789,582,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="167" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
superficially, and the differences between them are stated in the diagnosis of the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
